The paper deals with structured prediction tasks in computer vision, specifically semantic segmentation, monocular depth estimation, and surface normal prediction. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new framework for training structured prediction networks using an adversarial process, which involves training a structure analyzer. This involves machine learning techniques such as generative adversarial networks (GANs) and neural networks, which are commonly studied in sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of structured priors, which is a topic commonly studied in sub-categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
